      "widgets_values": [
        "MERGE #2 — Interior Room (base) + Relief Mesh (furniture/clutter)\n\nScenario: an interior shot where the room shell itself (floor,\nwalls, ceiling) is genuinely orthogonal/Manhattan, but the room is\nfurnished — sofas, lamps, plants, anything organic or angled that\nAtlasDeriveInteriorRoom's room_cuboid fit can't represent (it only\noutputs up to 4 walls + floor/ceiling aligned to the dominant wall\ndirection; forcing furniture into that fit would skew it).\n\n1. Node 4 (base) — AtlasDeriveInteriorRoom for the clean orthogonal\n   shell. No wall-count widget: room_cuboid always resolves its own\n   wall count from the depth map's Manhattan structure.\n2. Node 5 (clutter) — AtlasDeriveReliefMesh, which follows actual\n   depth contours vertex-by-vertex — no orthogonality assumption,\n   so it captures furniture/clutter shapes the room fit can't.\n   relief_quality=medium (256) for enough density on small objects.\n3. Node 6 — AtlasMergeGeometry combines them; solve_a (the room\n   shell) provides the merged camera.\n\nNote the depth_model on nodes 2/3 is switched to Indoor — match this\nby hand on any interior shot (nodes don't cross-configure each\nother's widgets)."
      ]
    }
